<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="3" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/597: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)<note n="10" xml:id="d3fn10">The same
                                telegram was sent on the same date to the Embassy in Japan as No.
                                2.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-07T19:00:00-05:00">January 7, 1936—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4. 1. Under date January 6 Davis telegraphed from London as follows:</p>
                        <p>[Here follows the substance of telegram No. 34, printed on <ref target="#pg_1">page 1</ref>.]</p>
                        <p>2. Department has had no information from any other source indicating
                            that there are in progress negotiations such as Craigie described.</p>
                        <p>3. Please cable Department your comments and any information
                            pertinent.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>